    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-05-06T09:18:17+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-06T09:18:17+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-05T23:48:17Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-05T23:48:17Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A ridge of high pressure over SA will weaken briefly as a cold front crosses the southeast of the state on Wednesday afternoon. The ridge will re-establish over SA in the wake of the front and stabilise over SA as the main high pressure centre moves over waters south of the Bight over the weekend. The high will then move eastwards early next week to be centred southeast of Tasmania late Tuesday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW012" description="Lower Eyre Peninsula" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-05-06T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-05T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. Medium chance of showers, becoming less likely in the evening. Winds west to southwesterly 15 to 25 km/h turning southerly 25 to 35 km/h in the early afternoon. Daytime maximum temperatures around 20.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 10:50am to 1:50pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-05-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-05-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-05-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-05-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. Slight chance of a shower. Winds southerly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching around 17.</text>
